Create a file in Desktop
open the terminal 
update the pc using this command "sudo apt update"
install ssh in this command "sudo apt install ssh"
check the status of ssh using this command "sudo systemctl status ssh"
Start the ssh in terminal "sudo systemctl start ssh"
type scp in terminal "scp" then the file you want to share in other pc "Hellopc2" then the desitnation username "mata@" then the ipadd of the destination pc "192.168.1.5" then the directory you want to share "/home/mata/Desktop " 
then the terminal ask the pasword of destination pc
then type y to yes
then thats it check the destination pc and the file you share enjoy
